# meta-uthp Layer

This README file contains information on the contents of the meta-uthp layer.

Please see the corresponding sections below for details.

## Dependencies

The meta-uthp layer depends on the following layers:

- **URI**: core  
  **branch**: scarthgap

- **URI**: meta-openembedded/meta-python 
  **branch**: scarthgap

- **URI**: meta-python2
  **branch**: master / close to scarthgap

- **URI**: networking-layer (meta-openembedded/meta-networking)
  **branch**: scarthgap

- **URI**: jupyter-layer
  **branch**: master / close to scarthgap

- **URI**: arm-toolchain  
  **branch**: scarthgap

- **URI**: meta-arm  
  **branch**: scarthgap

- **URI**: meta-ti-bsp  
  **branch**: scarthgap

- **URI**: meta-ti-extras  
  **branch**: scarthgap

## Table of Contents

  I. Adding the meta-uthp layer to your build  
 II. Misc

## I. Adding the meta-uthp layer to your build

Run the following command to add the meta-uthp layer to your build:

```sh
bitbake-layers add-layer meta-uthp
```

Add the following to your `conf/layer.conf`:

```sh
# We have a conf and classes directory, add to BBPATH
BBPATH .= ":${LAYERDIR}"

# We have recipes-* directories, add to BBFILES
BBFILES += "${LAYERDIR}/recipes-*/*/*.bb \
            ${LAYERDIR}/recipes-*/*/*.bbappend"

BBFILE_COLLECTIONS += "meta-uthp"
BBFILE_PATTERN_meta-uthp = "^${LAYERDIR}/"
BBFILE_PRIORITY_meta-uthp = "98"

LAYERDEPENDS_meta-uthp = "core meta-python meta-python2 networking-layer jupyter-layer arm-toolchain meta-arm meta-ti-bsp meta-ti-extras"
LAYERSERIES_COMPAT_meta-uthp = "scarthgap"
```

## II. Misc

The meta-uthp layer provides a comprehensive set of functionalities for integrating various tools and libraries, including Python support, networking, Jupyter, ARM toolchains, and support for the beaglebone black. This layer is compatible with the "scarthgap" series.

